text:
I often hear from Nebraskans who are tired of chaos. Moving from crisis to crisis is no way to govern. Enough with the distractions — we have work to do. 

@SpeakerMcCarthy is a friend and proven leader who never gives up, exactly what our country needs to get back on track.
I voted for today’s bill to pay our military and keep the government open while we finish regular appropriations bills. Now it’s time to get back to work.

I’m committed to cutting spending, securing our border, and putting our country on a better fiscal path. But not paying the men and women who serve our country and shutting down services Nebraskans rely on while we do our work is not the way.
Today, members of the Nebraska Press Association visited my office to discuss the valuable role the newspapers and publications of #NE03 play in our communities.
I was glad to join a @Heritage panel to discuss practical solutions to education reform. My bill, the Educational Choice for Children Act, would expand families' access to high-quality education.
It has been a joy to celebrate the 80th year of the Nebraska Breakfast with attendees from across our great state. This map shows the hometowns of those who have joined us in Washington.
